pseudepigrapha is a noun, means spurious or pseudonymous writings, especially Jewish writings ascribed to various biblical patriarchs and prophets but composed within approximately 200 years of the birth of Christ 
spurious假的；伪造的 伪作patriarch祖先
we will allude briefly to the main points.
我们将简单提及要点。allude暗示，间接提到；暗指 略加提及 
she had a way of alluding to Jean but never saying her name.
她有办法影射琼而不提及她的名字。allude暗示，间接提到；暗指 略加提及 
exiles of the Dispersion
exile流放；流亡；放逐 Dispersion分散；散布 
some seeds rely on birds for dispersion.
有些种子靠鸟来传播。Dispersion分散；散布 
he knew now that he would die in exile.
这下他明白他会在流亡中死去。exile流放；流亡；放逐 
live in reverent fear during the time of your exile
reverent恭敬的，虔敬的 
a reverent silence.
满怀敬意的肃静。reverent恭敬的，虔敬的 
Exhortations to live blameless lives may suggest that the Christian addressees were accused of immoral behavior, and exhortations to civil obedience perhaps imply that they were accused of disloyalty to governing powers.
exhortation劝告；规劝 劝告；规劝 addressee（尤指信件）收件人
exhortations to consumers to switch off electrical appliances.
规劝消费者关掉电器的话。exhortation劝告；规劝 劝告；规劝 
no amount of exhortation had any effect.
劝说一点用都没有。exhortation劝告；规劝 劝告；规劝 
As emperor, Domitian assumed totalitarian characteristics, thought he could be a new Augustus, and tried to make a personal cult of himself. 
assume僭取；夺取 呈现；具有 假装 totalitarian极权主义者cult膜拜；膜拜仪式 狂热崇拜；迷信 
the cult of the pursuit of money as an end in itself.
为了追逐金钱本身而去盲目拜金。cult膜拜；膜拜仪式 狂热崇拜；迷信 





